# ============================================
# AcaDesk Environment Variables
# ============================================
#
# USAGE:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local for local development:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. For production deployment:
#    - Set these variables in your hosting platform (Vercel, Railway, etc.)
#    - NEVER commit .env.local or .env.production with real values
#
# ============================================

# -------------------------
# Supabase Configuration (Required)
# -------------------------
# Get these from: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API
#
# DEVELOPMENT: Use your development/staging project
# PRODUCTION: Use your production project (different from dev)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# -------------------------
# Application Settings (Required)
# -------------------------
# Full URL of your application (include protocol, no trailing slash)
#
# DEVELOPMENT: http://localhost:3000
# PRODUCTION: https://your-domain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# -------------------------
# Optional: Supabase Service Role Key
# -------------------------
# Only use this for server-side operations that bypass RLS
# NEVER expose this key to the client
# NEVER commit this key to git
#
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key_here

# -------------------------
# Optional: Error Monitoring (Sentry)
# -------------------------
# Enable error reporting and monitoring in production
# Get your DSN from: https://sentry.io/settings/projects/
#
# DEVELOPMENT: Set to 'false' or omit to disable
# PRODUCTION: Set to 'true' and provide DSN
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ERROR_REPORTING_ENABLED=false
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-dsn@sentry.io/project-id

# -------------------------
# Development Checklist
# -------------------------
# Before starting development:
# ✓ Copy this file to .env.local
# ✓ Replace all placeholder values with your Supabase credentials
# ✓ Ensure Supabase project is created and accessible
# ✓ Run migrations: see SETUP.md

# -------------------------
# Production Checklist
# -------------------------
# Before deploying to production:
# ✓ Use PRODUCTION Supabase project credentials (separate from dev)
# ✓ NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL uses HTTPS protocol
# ✓ Supabase RLS policies are enabled and tested
# ✓ Environment variables are set in hosting platform dashboard
# ✓ Domain is properly configured with SSL certificate
# ✓ Test all authentication flows in production environment
# ✓ NEVER commit .env.production with real values

# -------------------------
# Security Notes
# -------------------------
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables are exposed to the browser
# - Supabase anon key is safe to expose (protected by RLS)
# - All data access MUST be protected by RLS policies
# - Service role key (if used) should ONLY be in server-side code
# - Always use separate Supabase projects for dev/staging/production
